# Create Jenkins API client with auth

Implement HTTP client module for Jenkins API integration with authentication, job operations, and build management.

## Requirements

- [ ] Create `lib/pag_server/integrations/jenkins/client.ex` module
- [ ] Implement Jenkins API authentication using:
  - [ ] Basic auth (username/API token)
  - [ ] API token management and refresh
- [ ] Define HTTP request builder functions:
  - [ ] Trigger job build with parameters
  - [ ] Get job status and build info
  - [ ] Retrieve build logs and console output
  - [ ] Cancel running builds
- [ ] Implement error handling for API failures and Jenkins-specific errors
- [ ] Add request/response logging and telemetry tracking
- [ ] Write comprehensive module tests with HTTP mocking

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Client module compiles with no warnings
- [ ] Supports Jenkins API endpoints (job triggers, build queries)
- [ ] Implements retry logic for transient failures
- [ ] API rate limiting handled gracefully
- [ ] All HTTP calls include telemetry span tracking
- [ ] Error responses parsed and wrapped in standardized error tuples
- [ ] Unit tests cover happy path and error scenarios
- [ ] `mix test` passes for all client tests
- [ ] `mix lint` passes without warnings


